<Class name="CM_DeckLayerLayout" id="bfaa0382-38a5-4aee-8bc8-b4301e353d32">
    <superclass name="CM_Object"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>

########################
#### ROTATION ############
########################

Rotation of ROROLocnDefn positions are handled in 4 groupings:

1X3 2X3 1X5 2X5

The positions are 20 foot long, the groupings are always by teh 20 foot length of the positions.

The group to be rotated have a rotation master that is always teh bottom left hand corner of the group.

Only the master need be selected and then the grouping chosen.

Positions can be grouped in actual and load views.

the 2 views are seperate.

the same group can be rotated in both views.

however if a group is rotated in actual the positions in that group can only be rotated in teh same grouping in load view.


</text>
    <DbClassMap file="vesselStructures"/>
